I"X<p>The <code>ted 5000</code> monitors electricity consumption/production by connecting to the <a href="https://www.theenergydetective.com/home">TED</a> gateway, itself connected to one or several Measuring Transmitting Units (MTU). The platform creates up to two sensors per MTU, one for Wattage the other for Voltage.</p>
<p>If you want to enable the ted5000 sensor, add the following lines to your <code>configuration.yaml</code>:</p>
<pre><code class="language-yaml"># Example configuration.yaml entry
sensor:
  - platform: ted5000
    host: 192.168.1.100
</code></pre>
<div class="config-vars">
  <h3><a class="title-link" name="configuration-variables" href="#configuration-variables"></a> Configuration Variables</h3>
  <dl class=''><dt><a class='title-link' name='host' href='#host'></a> host</dt><dd><p class='desc'><span class='type'>(<span class='string'>string</span>)</span><span class='required'>(Required)</span><span class='description'><p>The IP address of your ted gateway.</p>
</span></p></dd><dt><a class='title-link' name='port' href='#port'></a> port</dt><dd><p class='desc'><span class='type'>(<span class='integer'>integer</span>)</span><span class='required'>(Optional)</span><span class='description'><p>The port of your ted gateway.</p>
</span></p><p class='default'>
Default value: <p>80</p>
</p></dd><dt><a class='title-link' name='name' href='#name'></a> name</dt><dd><p class='desc'><span class='type'>(<span class='string'>string</span>)</span><span class='required'>(Optional)</span><span class='description'><p>Name of the ted gateway.</p>
</span></p><p class='default'>
Default value: <p>ted</p>
</p></dd></dl>
</div>
<p>For each plugged MTU, using an index starting at 1, the platform creates 2 sensors:</p>
<pre><code class="language-yaml">sensor.&lt;name&gt;_mtu&lt;MTU id&gt;_power
sensor.&lt;name&gt;_mtu&lt;MTU id&gt;_voltage
</code></pre>
:ET